  "prompt": "Do all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE?",
  "response": "Not all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE), but most modern smartphones do. Bluetooth 4.0, which introduced BLE, was released in 2010. Since then, it has become a standard feature in many devices due to its efficiency and lower power consumption compared to previous Bluetooth versions. \n\nHowever, older smartphones or very low-end models may not support Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE. If you're using a relatively recent smartphone, it's likely to include this feature, but it's always a good idea to check the specific specifications of your device to be sure.",
